KA.definition: you (sg.): the enclitic nominative of SIKA.

KA-.definition: a ligature prefixed to mensural nouns preceded by a numeral. a prefix that combines with (1) the full nominative pronouns with DA-to form the corresponding oblique pronouns, (2) the indefinite pronoun DATAO to form its oblique, and (3) the plural article and demonstrative pronouns to form their oblique.
KA-.cross_reference: KANYA-, KEN-, KENUA-. a prefix which occurs with adjective roots forming verb stems which in turn take the verbalizing affix -EN to form verbs meaning (1) to make like what the adjective root describes when the subject is a noun phrase, and (2) to do in the manner described by the adjective root when the subject is a verb phrase. + R1-, nom. af. the doing of the action expressed by the verb continuously. Nabisinanak ti kauuray kenka. I went hungry waiting for you

KA-.definition: a verbalizing affix which places the reciprocal actor or accessory of the action expressed by the verb in focus or subject position. a nominalizing affix occurring with adjective roots which expresses the degree or extent of the quality or trait indicated by the root. a nominalizing affix which occurs with verb steins and nouns.
KA-.ilok_example: With verb stems, it expresses the performance of the action expressed by the verb stem together with someone or close to someone; with nouns, it expresses the sharing of the object referred to be the noun with someone, or being or living in the place referred to by the noun with someone. +R1, a prefix occurring with verb stems which indicates recent completion of the action expressed by the verb stem.
KA-.origin: pt. KINA-, prp. KA- + R1, ptp. KINA- + R1
variations: KAI- R1. + R2 + -AN, var. of KA--AN

KA--AN.definition: a verbalizing affix occurring with numeral roots which expresses the meaning: to increase or bring to the number indicated by the numeral stem. a nominalizing affix occurring with temporal nouns which expresses the meaning: at the actual time of the period or event indicated by the noun stem. the superlative affix of adjectives: most.
variations: KA- + R1 + -AN the superlative adjectival affix

KA--AN + R1. a nominalizing affix occurring with nouns which indicates the place where the objects referred to by its noun stem are numerous or plentiful. + R1, var. of the superlative adjective affix KA--AN
